{"title":"The First Cervélo eBike Changes from Road to Gravel In a Flash","link":"https://bikerumor.com/cervelo-rouvida-ebike-changes-from-road-to-gravel/","date":1701763200000,"content":"<p><img width=\"2560\" height=\"1708\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-gravel-hero-2--scaled.jpeg\" alt=\"Cervelo Rouvida gravel hero 2\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-gravel-hero-2--scaled.jpeg 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-gravel-hero-2--297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-gravel-hero-2--800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-gravel-hero-2--120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-gravel-hero-2--768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-gravel-hero-2--1536x1025.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-gravel-hero-2--2048x1366.jpeg 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-gravel-hero-2--720x480.jpeg 720w\" /></p>\n<p>Cervélo has entered the eBike world; its all-new Rouvida looks to shake things up on and off the road. The design incorporates a new removable dropout piece that can quickly change from road bike to gravel geo. Cervélo notes this interchangeable design is much more than a ‘flip-chip’. The different dropouts rotate the entire frame to achieve a different fit and changes in handling.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-road-hero-scaled.jpeg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"534\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-road-hero-800x534.jpeg\" alt=\"Cervelo Rouvida road hero\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-road-hero-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-road-hero-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-road-hero-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-road-hero-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-road-hero-1536x1025.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-road-hero-2048x1366.jpeg 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-road-hero-720x480.jpeg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2>Cervélo Rouvida – What is it?</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>The Cervélo Rouvida is an all-new eBike from the famed Jumbo Visma (soon to be Team Visma | Lease a Bike) bike supplier. The Rouvida is available in a road-focused and a dedicated gravel version. It employs the Fazua Ride 60 motor, tuned explicitly to Cervélo’s specifications.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-gralve-hero--scaled.jpeg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"534\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-gralve-hero--800x534.jpeg\" alt=\"Cervelo Rouvida gralve hero\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-gralve-hero--800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-gralve-hero--297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-gralve-hero--120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-gralve-hero--768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-gralve-hero--1536x1025.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-gralve-hero--2048x1366.jpeg 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-gralve-hero--720x480.jpeg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/20230929_Powers_Cervelo_Gravel_0101-scaled.jpg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"534\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/20230929_Powers_Cervelo_Gravel_0101-800x534.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/20230929_Powers_Cervelo_Gravel_0101-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/20230929_Powers_Cervelo_Gravel_0101-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/20230929_Powers_Cervelo_Gravel_0101-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/20230929_Powers_Cervelo_Gravel_0101-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/20230929_Powers_Cervelo_Gravel_0101-1536x1025.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/20230929_Powers_Cervelo_Gravel_0101-2048x1366.jpg 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/20230929_Powers_Cervelo_Gravel_0101-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/20230929_Powers_Cervelo_Gravel_0061-scaled.jpg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"534\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/20230929_Powers_Cervelo_Gravel_0061-800x534.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/20230929_Powers_Cervelo_Gravel_0061-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/20230929_Powers_Cervelo_Gravel_0061-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/20230929_Powers_Cervelo_Gravel_0061-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/20230929_Powers_Cervelo_Gravel_0061-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/20230929_Powers_Cervelo_Gravel_0061-1536x1025.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/20230929_Powers_Cervelo_Gravel_0061-2048x1366.jpg 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/20230929_Powers_Cervelo_Gravel_0061-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>Cervélo Rouvida Road vs. Gravel Geo</h3>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>0.7° slacker head tube angle for gravel off-road handling</li>\n\n\n\n<li>The trail is 57.9mm for Road and 62mm for Gravel</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Tire clearance – 43.5mm for Gravel and 34mm for Road</li>\n\n\n\n<li>The stack is 7mm taller, and the reach is 5mm shorter with the gravel setup</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p><em>*Note the Cervélo Rouvida frame is the same (though the road/gravel have some aesthetic differences), and the geometry change comes from the interchangeable dropouts. Gravel and road dropouts will be available aftermarket from Cervélo for $80. </em></p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-gravel-geo.jpeg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"404\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-gravel-geo-800x404.jpeg\" alt=\"Cervelo Rouvida gravel geo\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-gravel-geo-800x404.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-gravel-geo-297x150.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-gravel-geo-120x61.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-gravel-geo-768x388.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-gravel-geo-1536x776.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-gravel-geo.jpeg 1766w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>Cervélo Rouvida Geometry</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The Cervelo Rouvida frame comes in Small (51cm) Medium (54cm) Large (56cm) and Extra Large (58cm).</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-geo-raod-.jpeg\"><img width=\"1848\" height=\"804\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-geo-raod-.jpeg\" alt=\"Cervelo Rouvida geo raod\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-geo-raod-.jpeg 1848w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-geo-raod--297x129.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-geo-raod--800x348.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-geo-raod--120x52.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-geo-raod--768x334.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-geo-raod--1536x668.jpeg 1536w\" /></a><figcaption>Cervelo Rouvida Raod Geometry </figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-geo-gravel-.jpeg\"><img width=\"1632\" height=\"798\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-geo-gravel-.jpeg\" alt=\"Cervelo Rouvida geo gravel\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-geo-gravel-.jpeg 1632w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-geo-gravel--297x145.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-geo-gravel--800x391.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-geo-gravel--120x59.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-geo-gravel--768x376.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-geo-gravel--1536x751.jpeg 1536w\" /></a><figcaption>Cervelo Rouvida Gravel Geometry </figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>What’s under the hood?</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>Fazua Motors’ latest offering, the Ride 60, has already received accolades for its ability to blend seamlessly with riders’ pedaling input to deliver a ride that feels like an analog bike, just with a lot more oomph.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-bb--scaled.jpeg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"534\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-bb--800x534.jpeg\" alt=\"Cervelo Rouvida bb\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-bb--800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-bb--297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-bb--120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-bb--768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-bb--1536x1025.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-bb--2048x1366.jpeg 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-bb--720x480.jpeg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The design team at Cervélo gave the Ride 60 some tweaks to give it a little more Cervélo flavor. The result is an ebike that keeps the Cervélo aesthetic and aerodynamics. The Cervélo design team claims the model’s vertical battery orientation is wind tunnel-proven to improve aerodynamics.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-logo-down-tube--scaled.jpeg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"534\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-logo-down-tube--800x534.jpeg\" alt=\"Cervelo Rouvida logo down tube\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-logo-down-tube--800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-logo-down-tube--297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-logo-down-tube--120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-logo-down-tube--768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-logo-down-tube--1536x1025.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-logo-down-tube--2048x1366.jpeg 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-logo-down-tube--720x480.jpeg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Cervélo uses Road Control, a unique Fazua proprietary setup, to give the rider easy access to control power and assistance. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-control-pods--scaled.jpeg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"552\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-control-pods--800x552.jpeg\" alt=\"Cervelo Rouvida control pods\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-control-pods--800x552.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-control-pods--297x205.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-control-pods--120x83.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-control-pods--768x530.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-control-pods--1536x1060.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-control-pods--2048x1414.jpeg 2048w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>If you’re running low on power for your light and want to take advantage of Rouvida’s extra battery life, the indicator panel on the top tube includes a USB charging port for lights or accessories.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-neon-scaled.jpeg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"534\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-neon-800x534.jpeg\" alt=\"Cervelo Rouvida neon\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-neon-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-neon-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-neon-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-neon-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-neon-1536x1025.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-neon-2048x1366.jpeg 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-neon-720x480.jpeg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Class 1 for the UK/EU and Class 3 for the North America </strong></p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>For the USA, the Class 3 Fazua Ride 60 has a <strong>28mph</strong> max assisted speed with a 450w max power and 430wh max battery capacity.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>For the UK/EU, the Class 1 Fazua Ride 60 has a <strong>25km/h</strong> max assisted speed with a 450w max power and 430wh max battery capacity.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<h2>Cervélo Rouvida Specs</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>The Cervélo Rouvida will be available in four different build options. Two are road-focused, and two are gravel-focused.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-shifters--scaled.jpeg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"534\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-shifters--800x534.jpeg\" alt=\"Cervelo Rouvida shifters\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-shifters--800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-shifters--297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-shifters--120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-shifters--768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-shifters--1536x1025.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-shifters--2048x1366.jpeg 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-shifters--720x480.jpeg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Rouvida Road</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>The flagship Cervélo Rouvida road model arrives with a SRAM Red AXS XPLR groupset, Reserve 44 wheels, and Vittoria NEXT tires. The crankset is an FSA CK-703 carbon e-bike-specific setup with a 10-44T SRAM cassette.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-seatpost--scaled.jpeg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"534\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-seatpost--800x534.jpeg\" alt=\"Cervelo Rouvida seatpost\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-seatpost--800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-seatpost--297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-seatpost--120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-seatpost--768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-seatpost--1536x1025.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-seatpost--2048x1366.jpeg 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-seatpost--720x480.jpeg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The second-tier Rouvida model comes equipped with SRAM Rival AXS XPLR groupset, Fulcrum Racing 600 wheels, and Vittoria NEXT ties. The crankset is the same FSA CK-703 but trades carbon for the alloy model.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida--scaled.jpeg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"534\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida--800x534.jpeg\" alt=\"Cervelo Rouvida\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida--800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida--297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida--120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida--768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida--1536x1025.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida--2048x1366.jpeg 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida--720x480.jpeg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Cervélo Rouvida Gravel</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>The Cervélo Rouvida gravel models come with more gravel-focused gear. The flagship Rouvida gravel model comes with a SRAM Force AXS XPLR setup, 10-44T cassette, Reserve 44 wheels, and WTF Vulpine 700x40mm tires. The cockpit gets a slight tweak from a traditional road bar to the Cervelo gravel bar with a 16 deg flare. The top Cervélo Rouvida gravel model also comes with a SRAM AXS Reverb dropper post to get dialed on the trails.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-charging-port--scaled.jpeg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"534\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-charging-port--800x534.jpeg\" alt=\"Cervelo Rouvida charging port\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-charging-port--800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-charging-port--297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-charging-port--120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-charging-port--768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-charging-port--1536x1025.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-charging-port--2048x1366.jpeg 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-charging-port--720x480.jpeg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The secondary Cervélo Rouvida model comes with a Shimano GRX 12-speed setup with a 10-45 cassette to climb anything. The wheels are Fulcrum Rapid Red 900 gravel wheels with WTB Vulpine tires. The cockpit is a Zipp Service Course bar with 5 deg flare and 11 deg outsweep. No dropper for this model… sorry.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-close-up-top-tube--scaled.jpeg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"534\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-close-up-top-tube--800x534.jpeg\" alt=\"Cervelo Rouvida close up top tube\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-close-up-top-tube--800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-close-up-top-tube--297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-close-up-top-tube--120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-close-up-top-tube--768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-close-up-top-tube--1536x1025.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-close-up-top-tube--2048x1366.jpeg 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Cervelo-Rouvida-close-up-top-tube--720x480.jpeg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>Cervélo Rouvida Pricing</h3>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Rouvida Road:</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>SRAM Red build $13,000</li>\n\n\n\n<li>SRAM Rival build: $7,500</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Rouvida Gravel</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>SRAM Force build: $9,800</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Shimano GRX build: $6,200</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>For more information, or to purchase, check out <a href=\"https://www.cervelo.com/en-US/bikes/rouvida\">Cervelo.com</a></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/cervelo-rouvida-ebike-changes-from-road-to-gravel/\">The First Cervélo eBike Changes from Road to Gravel In a Flash</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Jordan Villella","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"9acdd40919dcc405e8cfbbe5545876fe4a872e5463d92d625a2cb7f0ec309d0a","category":"Cycling"}